memtest86 (3.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release (Closes: #418939).
  * Updated debian/watch for new website layout.
  * In non-interactive mode, don't ask the user whether to run lilo on
    update (Holger Mense - Closes: #383635).
  * Fixed typo in extended description (Adrian Knoth - Closes: #377727).
  * Reference memtester instead of sysutils in Suggests and extended
    description (Benjamin Mesing - Closes: #372570).
  * Rework extended description some more: memtest86+ is not any more
    "more actively maintained upstream", and probably noone cares about
    the old history of this package and memmxtest.
  * Sync packaging with memtest86+-1.70:
    * added note about assumed fs layout in grub conf example.
    * avoid non-portable "read -p" in postinst.
    * avoid non-portable "-o" in test(1) call in postinst.
    * use dh-buildinfo.
  * Remove build-dependency on gcc-3.2, build with current gcc.
  * Switch to debhelper v5 (no change).
  * Updated FSF address in debian/copyright.
  * Bumped Standards-Version to 3.7.2 (no change).

